++++
Carp
++++

Carp is for code templates.  It cuts down on typing, so you won't get
CARP-al tunnel.  Harharhar.

Examples
========

Create a new script from a template
-----------------------------------

::

    $ carp --define foo=matt bar=robot script_template > script

Merges the template named script_template with the definitions from
the command line.

You either need to provide the path to the script_template or it
needs to be one of the stored templates.

List stored templates
---------------------

::

    $ carp-list

Lists the templates stored in the carpdir.

Store a template
----------------

::

    $ carp-store path-to-template

Provide a name for the template, and it is stored!

carp-inspect-template cliscript
    dumps out the template and lists the required keys.

Project status
==============

vaporware.

